## Korean landing-page strings for Contract Studio.
##
## NOTE: Most msgstrs are intentionally empty. Korean legal-product copy
## is high-stakes — machine translation routinely picks the wrong honorific
## register or uses near-synonyms that read as unprofessional to lawyers.
## We'll commission a native-speaker pass before flipping the language
## switcher on. Until then Gettext falls back to the English msgid.
##
## Where a Korean term is already part of the brand (법제처, 조문, etc.)
## we *do* translate, because the surrounding context is well-defined.
##
## TODO(Wave 3C2): native-speaker translation pass — keep voice formal-
## professional but not bureaucratic; target register matches court filings
## and law-firm intake forms.
msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Language: ko\n"
"Plural-Forms: nplurals=1; plural=0;\n"

